Correct Ans: 9. In R, `next` is a reserved word, which halts the processing of current iteration and advances the looping index. In the given example, the `if` condition is satisfied when `i` is equal to 5, because of `next` word, #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:14092021220020]

that particular iteration will be skipped and `for` loop will advance to next iteration. As we can see from the following code solution, the fifth iteration is skipped, So in total, the `"x"` is printed 9 times. [see_image_1] #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:14092021220020] https://t.co/GGLUcKpcxI
